0. Build the client and server.
tar -xvzf simple_messenger_1-0.tar.gz 
cd simple_messenger_1-0
make

1. Start server in one terminal window.
./server

2. Start client in the other terminal window.
./client localhost

3. Type in client, and the server should print what it receives to stdout.

4. Press control-c to exit client and server.



Example

TERMINAL 1

tar -xvzf simple_messenger_1-0.tar.gz 
cd simple_messenger_1-0/
make
./server
hello world
^C



TERMINAL 2

cd simple_messenger_1-0/
./client localhost
hello world
^C
